<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}-{8}{y}={18}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{y}=-{7}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({1},-{3}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --4. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{4}}{{-{{6}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{4}}}{{-{{6}}}}{\left(-{6}{x}+-{8}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{4}}}{{-{{6}}}}{\left({18}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{4}\right)}{x}+{5.3333333333333}{y}=-{12}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{y}=-{7}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6.3333333333333}{y}=-{19}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{19}}{{6.3333333333333}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{3}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+-{8}{\left(-{3}\right)}={18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{\left({24}\right)}={18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}={18}-{\left({24}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}=-{6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{6}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={1}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({1},-{3}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>